1
00:00:01,739 --> 00:00:03,840
You damn idiot.

2
00:00:06,677 --> 00:00:08,277
Who was it?

3
00:00:15,953 --> 00:00:17,353
Hey.

4
00:00:20,057 --> 00:00:24,825
Didn't I tell you not to do stupid things when working?

5
00:00:27,765 --> 00:00:29,599
What's wrong with you?

6
00:00:33,103 --> 00:00:34,603
I'm sorry, sir.

7
00:00:36,273 --> 00:00:37,673
Hey.

8
00:00:39,210 --> 00:00:44,377
Seokdae's cousin got beaten up by someone. So he went there.

9
00:00:44,377 --> 00:00:47,184
And he got beaten up instead?

10
00:00:48,085 --> 00:00:50,420
- He's not that beaten…
- Quiet.

11
00:00:58,829 --> 00:01:00,329
Okay.

12
00:01:03,033 --> 00:01:05,033
Let's make them pay ten times more.

13
00:01:05,033 --> 00:01:07,713
Yeah? Yes?

14
00:01:15,246 --> 00:01:17,557
Hey, let's make some money.

15
00:01:17,557 --> 00:01:19,483
I'll help you out.

16
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:36,790
[Park Ji Hoon]

17
00:01:36,790 --> 00:01:39,530
[Choi Hyeon Wook]

18
00:01:39,530 --> 00:01:42,110
[Hong Kyeong]

19
00:01:42,110 --> 00:01:44,070
[Lee Yeon]

20
00:01:44,070 --> 00:01:46,143
[Shin Seung Ho]

21
00:01:46,143 --> 00:01:49,900
[WEAK HERO CLASS 1]
♫ The heart that you take out after passing ♫

22
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:52,580
♫ It's an old regret ♫

23
00:01:52,580 --> 00:01:57,100
♫ It's already too late ♫

24
00:01:58,610 --> 00:02:01,630
♫ Words I didn't want to hear ♫

25
00:02:01,630 --> 00:02:04,700
♫ A face covered with a hand ♫

26
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:09,310
♫ I didn't know I'd miss you ♫

27
00:02:09,310 --> 00:02:21,370
♫ I regret it, let's not cry anymore ♫

28
00:02:21,370 --> 00:02:33,940
♫ Sigh. Please don't hide ♫

29
00:02:37,980 --> 00:02:41,430
[Original: SeoPass - Kim Jin Seok "Weak Hero"]

30
00:02:45,803 --> 00:02:48,071
Watch me nail this.

31
00:02:49,406 --> 00:02:51,006
- Okay.
- Impressive.

32
00:02:51,006 --> 00:02:52,608
Take ten out.

33
00:02:55,412 --> 00:02:57,981
Didn't we meet for the group project?

34
00:03:01,785 --> 00:03:03,585
Oh, that's right.

35
00:03:03,585 --> 00:03:05,221
Hey, Sieun.

36
00:03:05,221 --> 00:03:07,067
It's the weekend.

37
00:03:07,091 --> 00:03:12,793
You need to let your brain rest every now and then for it to perform better.

38
00:03:14,732 --> 00:03:16,250
You're not going to college, are you?

39
00:03:16,543 --> 00:03:18,868
That was close.

40
00:03:18,868 --> 00:03:20,847
Did you get shot in the head?

41
00:03:20,847 --> 00:03:23,273
Did you crawl into a chicken coop again?

42
00:03:23,273 --> 00:03:25,241
Come on. Hurry up.

43
00:03:27,778 --> 00:03:29,556
Just play already.

44
00:03:29,580 --> 00:03:31,448
You know you want to.

45
00:03:31,448 --> 00:03:33,316
Jeez, come on.

46
00:03:41,625 --> 00:03:43,103
Law of reflection.

47
00:03:43,103 --> 00:03:45,138
Based on the center of the billiard ball,

48
00:03:45,138 --> 00:03:47,882
the angles of incidence and reflection are equal.

49
00:03:47,882 --> 00:03:50,877
Angle of incidence, 35 degrees. Less than 3 degrees of error.

50
00:03:50,877 --> 00:03:53,737
The success rate is about 90 percent.

51
00:04:01,111 --> 00:04:02,511
Nice.

52
00:04:03,347 --> 00:04:05,448
Let's go work on the project.

53
00:04:09,954 --> 00:04:12,556
Where are you going? It's best of three.

54
00:04:12,556 --> 00:04:15,258
Make sure to set yours to 100 this time.

55
00:04:18,862 --> 00:04:21,207
I think the outcome will be the same.

56
00:04:21,207 --> 00:04:23,231
Jeez.

57
00:04:23,231 --> 00:04:24,911
Is that so?

58
00:04:24,911 --> 00:04:26,546
Do you think so?

59
00:04:26,546 --> 00:04:29,206
Then let's bet jajangmyeon and tangsuyuk, too.

60
00:04:29,206 --> 00:04:30,951
Stir-fried meat and vegetables?

61
00:04:30,951 --> 00:04:32,575
Deal?

62
00:04:37,848 --> 00:04:41,685
[Awesome Billiards]

63
00:04:41,685 --> 00:04:43,585
Darn it.

64
00:04:43,585 --> 00:04:45,255
[Awesome Billiards]

65
00:04:47,458 --> 00:04:50,492
- You know I let you win.
- No, you didn't.

66
00:04:50,492 --> 00:04:53,173
Gosh, I feel so pathetic.

67
00:04:53,173 --> 00:04:56,232
Forget it. Let's go have some beer.

68
00:04:56,232 --> 00:04:57,600
I need to go.

69
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:59,535
You guys go have fun.

70
00:04:59,535 --> 00:05:02,082
Come with us. It's my treat.

71
00:05:02,082 --> 00:05:05,146
I've fallen behind on my studies thanks to you guys.

72
00:05:05,146 --> 00:05:08,878
All right, then. Go home safely.

73
00:05:08,878 --> 00:05:12,615
You were lucky today. I won't go easy on you next time.

74
00:05:15,152 --> 00:05:16,763
But where are we drinking?

75
00:05:16,763 --> 00:05:20,290
Just follow me. Come on.

76
00:05:29,266 --> 00:05:31,378
[Registration]

77
00:05:31,378 --> 00:05:33,737
[Payment]

78
00:05:38,142 --> 00:05:41,142
Hey. What's with your arm?

79
00:05:43,881 --> 00:05:45,659
What do you mean?

80
00:05:45,659 --> 00:05:48,618
It's because of you, Yeongbin.

81
00:05:50,855 --> 00:05:52,455
Sorry?

82
00:05:53,757 --> 00:05:55,357
Who are you?

83
00:05:56,326 --> 00:06:01,598
None of your concern, but you need to do me a favor.

84
00:06:32,229 --> 00:06:34,165
Damn it. Why is he here?

85
00:06:34,165 --> 00:06:36,065
I'm dead meat.

86
00:06:37,835 --> 00:06:39,603
May I help…

87
00:06:40,871 --> 00:06:42,906
That'll be 13,000 won.

88
00:06:42,906 --> 00:06:44,217
Are you done?

89
00:06:44,217 --> 00:06:45,741
I couldn't find it.

90
00:06:45,741 --> 00:06:47,811
Here you go.

91
00:06:47,812 --> 00:06:50,814
I'm famished. Let's go. Thank you.

92
00:06:55,953 --> 00:06:59,222
What? It's raining cats and dogs.

93
00:07:00,224 --> 00:07:04,101
No way. How is this possible?

94
00:07:04,101 --> 00:07:05,861
Hey!

95
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:11,368
I don't have an umbrella.

96
00:07:15,406 --> 00:07:17,106
Walk me home.

97
00:07:17,106 --> 00:07:20,384
- Why should I?
- Because you have an umbrella and I don't.

98
00:07:20,384 --> 00:07:22,455
- Do you like tteokbokki?
- No.

99
00:07:22,455 --> 00:07:24,324
Now you do, right?

100
00:07:24,324 --> 00:07:26,428
I know a tasty tteokbokki place.

101
00:07:28,919 --> 00:07:30,754
It's really spicy.

102
00:07:32,556 --> 00:07:34,156
Hey.

103
00:07:35,059 --> 00:07:36,793
Can I please leave?

104
00:07:36,793 --> 00:07:38,661
No, you can't.

105
00:07:39,330 --> 00:07:42,432
- Why not?
- I can't eat alone.

106
00:07:43,801 --> 00:07:46,836
Why aren't you eating? You can't handle spicy food?

107
00:07:46,837 --> 00:07:48,638
Why would you eat this?

108
00:07:49,206 --> 00:07:51,174
You have no friends, right?

109
00:07:57,348 --> 00:07:59,182
This is my number. Save it.

110
00:07:59,182 --> 00:08:00,917
What's your name?

111
00:08:02,052 --> 00:08:03,652
Why?

112
00:08:05,723 --> 00:08:07,034
[Jerk]

113
00:08:07,034 --> 00:08:08,735
You're a jerk.

114
00:08:08,735 --> 00:08:10,660
You're just my type.

115
00:08:11,295 --> 00:08:13,697
I tend to like jerks.

116
00:08:16,066 --> 00:08:18,268
Thank you.

117
00:08:23,073 --> 00:08:24,841
See you next time.

118
00:08:24,841 --> 00:08:26,749
Sorry about the other day.

119
00:08:28,345 --> 00:08:30,047
I'm on my way.

120
00:08:30,047 --> 00:08:32,015
Okay, I'll hurry.

121
00:08:32,616 --> 00:08:34,116
Okay.

122
00:08:44,094 --> 00:08:45,405
Where's Yeongi ?

123
00:08:45,405 --> 00:08:47,297
She's on her way.

124
00:08:50,134 --> 00:08:52,612
- Darn it.
- Is Gilsu inside?

125
00:08:52,612 --> 00:08:54,336
Yes, he is.

126
00:08:55,306 --> 00:08:56,683
Good work, you scumbag.

127
00:08:56,683 --> 00:09:00,410
Some idiot handed over his mom's car today.

128
00:09:00,410 --> 00:09:03,580
- What a lunatic.
- Exactly.

129
00:09:04,482 --> 00:09:06,649
You bastard,

130
00:09:06,649 --> 00:09:09,352
I told you to pick up my calls.

131
00:09:10,087 --> 00:09:11,388
I'm sorry.

132
00:09:11,388 --> 00:09:12,788
So?

133
00:09:14,325 --> 00:09:16,559
How will you pay me back?

134
00:09:18,896 --> 00:09:21,264
I'll ask my mom for money.

135
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:25,602
You have three days.

136
00:09:25,603 --> 00:09:28,071
If you don't pay me back by then,

137
00:09:28,071 --> 00:09:32,152
I'll kill both of your parents

138
00:09:32,152 --> 00:09:34,644
and set your house on fire.

139
00:09:43,654 --> 00:09:45,154
Is the car in good condition?

140
00:09:45,154 --> 00:09:46,756
Yeah.

141
00:09:47,591 --> 00:09:50,126
Nice. Good job.

142
00:09:50,761 --> 00:09:52,672
That little scumbag.

143
00:09:52,672 --> 00:09:57,467
Beat him up for 30 more minutes before letting him go.

144
00:09:57,467 --> 00:09:59,736
Or just crush his leg or something.

145
00:10:15,052 --> 00:10:16,752
Quiet.

146
00:10:16,752 --> 00:10:18,889
What are you doing?

147
00:10:21,859 --> 00:10:23,603
- Let me see.
- Where?

148
00:10:23,627 --> 00:10:25,972
I'm getting one. Hey!

149
00:10:25,972 --> 00:10:28,498
I'll loot here.

150
00:10:28,498 --> 00:10:31,368
- Suho, the car.
- Get in.

151
00:10:31,368 --> 00:10:32,769
That's it?

152
00:10:32,769 --> 00:10:34,915
I'll eat his.

153
00:10:34,915 --> 00:10:37,150
- I want it.
- No, I want it.

154
00:10:37,150 --> 00:10:38,674
Sieun.

155
00:10:43,514 --> 00:10:45,915
Can we talk for a minute?

156
00:10:47,251 --> 00:10:49,119
I have nothing to say to you.

157
00:10:49,119 --> 00:10:51,688
Hey, what do you want?

158
00:10:56,060 --> 00:10:57,927
It won't take long.

159
00:11:03,801 --> 00:11:05,501
Help me.

160
00:11:07,104 --> 00:11:09,506
Please meet with my attorney.

161
00:11:10,674 --> 00:11:14,944
Please tell them that the fentanyl wasn't mine.

162
00:11:16,714 --> 00:11:18,614
Beomseok, you too.

163
00:11:21,051 --> 00:11:22,762
This is driving me crazy.

164
00:11:22,762 --> 00:11:25,388
I'm all that my mom has.

165
00:11:26,090 --> 00:11:28,324
Damn it.

166
00:11:28,324 --> 00:11:32,795
I'm begging you. They'll throw me into a juvenile detention center.

167
00:11:33,931 --> 00:11:36,399
Look at his crocodile tears.

168
00:11:38,135 --> 00:11:39,735
Sieun.

169
00:11:40,304 --> 00:11:43,172
Should we just testify?

170
00:11:43,172 --> 00:11:45,375
It's not a hard thing to do.

171
00:12:17,308 --> 00:12:18,808
Hey.

172
00:12:18,808 --> 00:12:20,844
Why the basement?

173
00:12:20,844 --> 00:12:23,012
This is a shortcut.

174
00:12:23,948 --> 00:12:26,116
You better not be lying to us.

175
00:12:26,116 --> 00:12:28,018
I'm not.

176
00:12:30,387 --> 00:12:31,987
Hurry up.

177
00:12:31,987 --> 00:12:35,402
- What should we have for dinner?
- I need to go to the academy later.

178
00:12:35,402 --> 00:12:38,705
Come on. Don't be ridiculous.

179
00:12:38,705 --> 00:12:42,541
Let's have some jjajangmyeon after this, then go to an internet café.

180
00:12:42,541 --> 00:12:44,478
Don't you need to work today?

181
00:12:44,478 --> 00:12:47,237
Do I? Darn it.

182
00:12:52,343 --> 00:12:54,444
I guess I won't be going to work.

183
00:13:01,085 --> 00:13:02,886
I saw this coming.

184
00:13:03,921 --> 00:13:07,357
Guys, nice to see you.

185
00:13:25,075 --> 00:13:28,044
Seokdae, this is them. Right?

186
00:13:28,879 --> 00:13:30,379
Yes, sir.

187
00:13:34,151 --> 00:13:36,029
As you already know,

188
00:13:36,029 --> 00:13:40,297
my dear Seokdae got hurt because of you guys.

189
00:13:40,891 --> 00:13:44,127
He's not even insured, you know?

190
00:13:44,127 --> 00:13:46,496
How could you beat him up like this?

191
00:13:46,496 --> 00:13:48,297
What do you want?

192
00:13:49,667 --> 00:13:51,901
I'll give you three days.

193
00:13:52,636 --> 00:13:55,438
Bring me 15 million won as settlement money.

194
00:13:57,274 --> 00:13:59,352
What are you talking about? Hey.

195
00:13:59,352 --> 00:14:01,277
What's with the cast?

196
00:14:01,277 --> 00:14:02,789
I never even touched your arm.

197
00:14:02,789 --> 00:14:06,593
Look what you've done to his arm.

198
00:14:06,593 --> 00:14:09,219
- But you don't remember.
- But…

199
00:14:10,321 --> 00:14:12,822
do you have proof that we did that?

200
00:14:17,528 --> 00:14:21,264
You guys are ridiculous.

201
00:14:21,264 --> 00:14:22,698
Hey.

202
00:14:24,368 --> 00:14:27,070
I kill people for money.

203
00:14:27,705 --> 00:14:29,649
I sometimes make them disabled.

204
00:14:29,649 --> 00:14:34,741
- Aren't you too old to be bragging about that?
- You scumbag.

205
00:14:38,949 --> 00:14:41,051
Do you think I'm joking?

206
00:14:43,687 --> 00:14:45,755
You have three days.

207
00:14:46,690 --> 00:14:49,325
If you don't bring it by then,

208
00:14:49,325 --> 00:14:51,962
you'll have to borrow some from me.

209
00:14:55,332 --> 00:14:57,367
You bastard.

210
00:14:59,904 --> 00:15:01,604
Let's go.

211
00:15:23,460 --> 00:15:25,295
Suho, are you okay?

212
00:15:26,964 --> 00:15:28,990
- No, I'm not. Damn it.
- Hang on.

213
00:15:31,730 --> 00:15:34,137
What do we do now?

214
00:15:34,137 --> 00:15:35,649
Who cares? They can't do anything.

215
00:15:35,673 --> 00:15:37,017
This hurts. Damn.

216
00:15:37,041 --> 00:15:40,177
[Seoul National University: 3 Admitted]

217
00:15:40,711 --> 00:15:43,146
Damn, what's wrong with my bike?

218
00:15:43,146 --> 00:15:45,114
It's not working?

219
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:51,120
There they are.

220
00:16:05,903 --> 00:16:07,647
I'll go if you're going.

221
00:16:07,647 --> 00:16:09,316
I'm going to go review at home.

222
00:16:09,316 --> 00:16:11,040
Hurry.

223
00:16:16,714 --> 00:16:18,214
Is it him?

224
00:17:08,999 --> 00:17:10,399
Hello?

225
00:17:10,399 --> 00:17:12,669
I need to talk to you.

226
00:17:12,669 --> 00:17:17,608
[Gunsoo Building]

227
00:17:37,561 --> 00:17:39,061
Who is he?

228
00:17:39,061 --> 00:17:40,397
What does he do?

229
00:17:40,397 --> 00:17:41,897
Who?

230
00:17:44,235 --> 00:17:47,935
You mean Gilsu?

231
00:17:50,307 --> 00:17:54,285
He's someone who puts a roof over our heads and gives us work.

232
00:17:54,285 --> 00:17:57,314
- Like what?
- This and that.

233
00:17:57,915 --> 00:17:59,783
Why do you ask?

234
00:18:05,589 --> 00:18:07,924
I'm in no position to say this.

235
00:18:10,594 --> 00:18:13,530
But be wary of him. He's a real scumbag.

236
00:18:14,632 --> 00:18:17,968
He wasn't lying when he said he killed people for money.

237
00:18:18,769 --> 00:18:22,005
He even has ties with a gang. A real gang.

238
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:26,142
He's obsessed with money. He'll do literally anything for it.

239
00:18:27,011 --> 00:18:28,021
So?

240
00:18:28,021 --> 00:18:31,447
So give him at least half of what he asked for.

241
00:18:31,447 --> 00:18:32,948
What if I don't?

242
00:18:33,851 --> 00:18:36,019
Then what?

243
00:18:41,826 --> 00:18:43,726
You'll be done for.

244
00:18:45,696 --> 00:18:48,264
You'll be done for like us.

245
00:18:57,041 --> 00:18:58,641
And if I do?

246
00:18:59,477 --> 00:19:00,977
What?

247
00:19:03,280 --> 00:19:05,180
Then will he stop?

248
00:19:11,021 --> 00:19:13,021
Are you okay with this?

249
00:20:16,054 --> 00:20:19,054
Hey, what is it?

250
00:20:19,054 --> 00:20:20,556
What's going on?

251
00:20:21,558 --> 00:20:24,194
What is this? I'm hungry.

252
00:20:26,764 --> 00:20:29,066
[Chemistry Lab]

253
00:20:34,672 --> 00:20:37,440
I'll put an end to it today.

254
00:20:38,475 --> 00:20:39,686
What?

255
00:20:39,686 --> 00:20:41,644
It's been three days.

256
00:20:46,350 --> 00:20:47,950
It's 15 million won.

257
00:20:49,954 --> 00:20:52,422
Let's give it to them and end it.

258
00:20:54,058 --> 00:20:55,858
What is this?

259
00:20:57,461 --> 00:21:00,764
- My parents gave it to me.
- Are you kidding me?

260
00:21:00,764 --> 00:21:03,633
They gave you 15 million won just like that?

261
00:21:03,633 --> 00:21:05,334
Where did you get it?

262
00:21:05,903 --> 00:21:08,038
Why does that matter?

263
00:21:08,038 --> 00:21:09,739
Answer me.

264
00:21:10,774 --> 00:21:12,475
Tell us.

265
00:21:15,579 --> 00:21:17,614
I sold my father's watch.

266
00:21:17,614 --> 00:21:20,160
But he had given it to me anyway.

267
00:21:20,160 --> 00:21:22,652
Look who the wacko is.

268
00:21:23,387 --> 00:21:27,023
Why pay that bastard? Let's just report him.

269
00:21:28,192 --> 00:21:31,561
Take this money and get that watch back.

270
00:21:32,096 --> 00:21:35,232
But he said it was useless to call the police.

271
00:21:35,866 --> 00:21:37,266
Beomseok.

272
00:21:38,302 --> 00:21:40,636
I appreciate your help.

273
00:21:40,636 --> 00:21:43,373
But I'll take care of it, so don't worry.

274
00:21:43,373 --> 00:21:45,708
What do you mean "you'll take care of it"?

275
00:21:45,708 --> 00:21:49,911
- Let's just call the police.
- Okay. I'll report him.

276
